The paper deals with the problem of ensuring privacy in electronic data sources, which is a core concern in the field of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also presents a framework for quantifying the utility-privacy tradeoff in databases, which involves modeling data (cs.DB), information theory (cs.IT), and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper discusses the modeling of prior knowledge, which is relevant to the field of artificial intelligence and machine learning (cs.SI).
